Marfrig Will More Than Double Meat Market Share, Valor Says

-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 
2011-12-09T11:47:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/marfrig-will-more-than-double-meat-market-share-valor-says.html
Marfrig Alimentos SA will more than
double its share of the Brazilian processed-meat market
following an asset swap with BRF - Brasil Foods SA, Valor
Economico reported, citing Marfrig’s chief executive officer.  Marfrig’s market share will rise to about 21 percent from 9
percent following the agreement announced yesterday, Marfrig CEO
Marcos Molina said, according to Sao Paulo-based Valor.  The asset-swap will also double production capacity at
Marfrig’s poultry and pork division, according to Valor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in Rio de Janeiro at 
 rorihuela@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  